.TH "_omap_calculate_ecc_bch" 9 "_omap_calculate_ecc_bch" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
_omap_calculate_ecc_bch \- Generate ECC bytes for one sector
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" _omap_calculate_ecc_bch
.BI "(struct mtd_info *mtd "  ","
.BI "const u_char *dat "  ","
.BI "u_char *ecc_calc "  ","
.BI "int i "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "mtd" 12
MTD device structure
.IP "dat" 12
The pointer to data on which ecc is computed
.IP "ecc_calc" 12
The ecc_code buffer
.IP "i" 12
The sector number (for a multi sector page)
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Support calculating of BCH4/8/16 ECC vectors for one sector
within a page. Sector number is in \fIi\fP.
